The malware may employ techniques from the MITRE ATT&CK framework related to Initial Access or Execution, although specific tactics or techniques are not explicitly detailed in the report. To mitigate the threat, enabling reliable antivirus solutions, ensuring systems are up-to-date with security patches, and monitoring network traffic for anomalous activities are recommended countermeasures. Community discussions are scarce; however, awareness and situational readiness could combat similar potential threats.
